USAGE:

    <cinematicText duration="$DURATION"
                   type="$TYPE">

                   Text ;
                   $COLOR|2nd line text  ;
                   </cinematicText>


    $DURATION       - How long, in milliseconds, the text will last for on screen (minus entrance and exit times if it is a fading text)
    $TYPE           - Type of cinematic text:
                        0:  Fading cinematic


    $COLOR          - Color of the text on that line, see Colours enum for values.


    example usage:

        <cinematicText duration="5000" type="0">
            YELLOW|Saya 1000 AD;
            ;
            3rd line text
        </cinematicText>